# Code Organization

The codebase follows a feature-based organization pattern:

## Main Directories
- [src/auth/](mdc:src/auth) - Authentication related components
- [src/components/](mdc:src/components) - Shared UI components
- [src/context/](mdc:src/context) - React context providers
- [src/events/](mdc:src/events) - Event management features
- [src/hooks/](mdc:src/hooks) - Custom React hooks
- [src/public/](mdc:src/public) - Public-facing components
- [src/services/](mdc:src/services) - Service integrations used to retrieve or write data
- [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils) - Utility functions

## Event Structure
Events are a core concept with subdirectories for:
- [src/events/actions/](mdc:src/events/actions) - Event-related actions
- [src/events/admin/](mdc:src/events/admin) - Admin interfaces, the most important service of the project.
- [src/events/page/](mdc:src/events/page) - Event page components

## Backend
- [functions/src/](mdc:functions/src) - Backend functions
- [functions/src/api/](mdc:functions/src/api) - API routes and handlers
